import os
import read

# list of files ending in .tif in 'munaretto/2022-11-21_Bortolon'
files = os.listdir('munaretto/2022-11-21_Bortolon')
processed = os.listdir('/home/maana/mp_2022_34_53/dimes')
processed = [file.split('.')[0] for file in processed]
for file in files:
    if file.endswith('.tif'):
        
        shot = file.split('_')[0]
        if shot in processed:
            print(f'now reading {file} - skip video already processed')
        else:
            print(f'now reading {file}')
            read.dimes_movie(f'munaretto/2022-11-21_Bortolon/{file}')

Average all frames of the fiducial and display, affine transform onto the floor map from A. McLean¶

import read
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import floor
import process
from IPython.display import display, Markdown, Latex

def affine_trans(coords_A, coords_B):
    #! coords_A and coords_B are lists of tuples of (x,y) coordinates
    #! returns the affine transformation matrix that maps from system A to B
    x,y,z = coords_A
    a,b,c = coords_B
    #! x,y,z are the source coordinates and a,b,c are the target coordinates
    #! the affine transformation matrix is given by:
    A = np.array([[a[0],b[0],c[0]],[a[1],b[1],c[1]],[1,1,1]])
    B_inv = np.linalg.inv(np.array([[x[0],y[0],z[0]],[x[1],y[1],z[1]],[1,1,1]]))
    M = np.matmul(A, B_inv)
    return M

def fiducial_transform(X,Y,Z):
    #! X,Y,Z are lists of lists of (x,y) coordinates
    #! X[0] is the pixel coordinate of DiMES head in the fiducial image
    #! X[1] is the (R,phi) coordinate of DiMES head
    #! Y[0] is the pixel coordinate of the point Y in the fiducial image
    #! Y[1] is the (R,phi) coordinate of the point Y
    #! Z[0] is the pixel coordinate of the point Z in the fiducial image
    #! Z[1] is the (R,phi) coordinate of the point Z
    #! returns the affine transformation matrix that maps from the fiducial image to the floor image
    coords_A = [X[0][0],X[0][1]], [Y[0][0],Y[0][1]], [Z[0][0],Z[0][1]]
    coords_B = pol_to_cart([X[1][0],X[1][1]]), process.pol_to_cart([Y[1][0],Y[1][1]]), process.pol_to_cart([Z[1][0],Z[1][1]])
    M = affine_trans(coords_A, coords_B)
    p,q,r = M[0]
    s,t,u = M[1]
    boundary = [[0,0], [640,0], [640,480], [0,480]]
    real_boundary = []
    for pt in boundary:
        x,y = pt
        real_boundary.append([p*x+q*y+r, s*x+t*y+u])
    # make a polygon from the real boundary
    real_boundary = np.array(real_boundary)
    poly = plt.Polygon(real_boundary, fill=False, edgecolor='red', linewidth=2)
    return M, poly

def pol_to_cart(polar_coords):
    R, phi = polar_coords
    #! 90-phi because thats what makes things line up on the floor image
    x = R*np.cos(np.deg2rad(90-phi))
    y = R*np.sin(np.deg2rad(90-phi))
    return x,y

fig, ax = plt.subplots(1,2,figsize=(15,15))
fig, ax, X, Y, Z = floor.fiducial_markup(fig,ax)
M, poly = fiducial_transform(X,Y,Z)
# show legend 
ax[0].legend(loc='best', bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1), fontsize=8)
  • image from DiMES TV Diagnostics page is used as a reference
